17:48.210 --> 17:49.899
I got this.

17:49.900 --> 17:51.749
Hunh! Ungh!

17:53.140 --> 17:55.960
Oh, I'm glad I captured
that for posterity.

17:56.020 --> 17:58.180
If you want something done right...

18:00.960 --> 18:06.599
- ♪ Ooh, ooh, o-o-oh ♪
- ♪ Holy, holy, holy ♪

18:06.600 --> 18:11.360
- ♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh ♪
- ♪ Lord, God Almighty ♪

18:11.500 --> 18:15.499
- ♪ Ooh, ooh, o-o-oh ♪
- ♪ Early in the morning ♪

18:15.500 --> 18:18.367
Mom's really nice when she
lives in the television.

18:18.368 --> 18:22.159
♪ ... to Thee ♪

18:22.160 --> 18:26.679
♪ Holy, Thou art holy ♪

18:26.680 --> 18:31.380
♪ There is none beside Thee ♪

18:31.381 --> 18:35.926
No! This is the worst thing
to happen to anyone ever!

18:35.927 --> 18:42.789
♪ ... in love and purity ♪

18:45.000 --> 18:46.879
More fan mail for me.

18:46.880 --> 18:48.340
Apparently I'm the reason

18:48.350 --> 18:50.619
"Barry from Culver City Renal Care"

18:50.620 --> 18:52.999
found the strength to soldier on.

18:53.000 --> 18:54.679
Although, he might just
be buttering me up

18:54.680 --> 18:55.946
for one of my kidneys.

18:55.947 --> 18:57.447
- Aww.
- Another one from prison.

18:57.448 --> 19:00.325
Says he's a "fan for life."

19:00.326 --> 19:02.669
I can't believe I got locked out.

19:02.670 --> 19:04.699
I still feel like William had
something to do with it.

19:04.700 --> 19:07.375
He did have motive and opportunity.

19:08.160 --> 19:10.819
- Oh. Here's one for you.
- Really?!

19:10.820 --> 19:12.749
One of your postcards came back.

19:12.750 --> 19:14.340
I don't think the producers
of "The Waltons"

19:14.350 --> 19:16.049
actually live on Walton's Mountain.

19:18.570 --> 19:20.779
Mom, I've been doing a lot of thinking.

19:20.780 --> 19:22.560
Yeah, and I said knock it off.

19:22.570 --> 19:24.349
You can pick whatever
godless cult you want to

19:24.350 --> 19:25.779
when you turn 18, but for now,

19:25.780 --> 19:27.209
every Sunday, you're in that pew

19:27.210 --> 19:28.687
gutting it out with the rest of us.

19:28.688 --> 19:30.550
I've realized what
happened to me at the show

19:30.560 --> 19:33.060
couldn't have just been an accident.

19:33.100 --> 19:35.260
God struck me mute,

19:35.270 --> 19:38.639
like the Angel Gabriel did to
Zachariah in the Gospel of Luke.

19:38.640 --> 19:39.908
You know the story.

19:39.909 --> 19:41.939
Sure. But... refresh me.

19:41.940 --> 19:44.600
Zachariah was punished
for his lack of faith.

19:44.620 --> 19:46.160
And maybe I was, too.

19:46.164 --> 19:48.332
So I'm back on board with Catholicism...

19:48.333 --> 19:50.250
mainly because I'm
scared to death of God.

19:50.251 --> 19:52.499
Oh, sweetie.

19:54.170 --> 19:56.619
You finally get it.

19:56.620 --> 19:57.660
Mm.

20:00.000 --> 20:01.499
I got 'em.

20:01.500 --> 20:03.931
Now the question is,
what do I do with them?

20:03.932 --> 20:06.240
Give them to Eddie and Joey?

20:06.250 --> 20:08.400
And then wait 2 1/2 hours
to give us a ride home?

20:09.260 --> 20:10.810
I pushed it too far, didn't I?

20:10.813 --> 20:12.147
All right. Here you go.

20:12.148 --> 20:13.524
- Oh!
- Oh, hang on.

20:13.525 --> 20:15.379
These tickets are worth $7?

20:15.380 --> 20:18.029
What do they do, come over after
the concert and paint your house?

20:18.030 --> 20:19.079
That's only face value.

20:19.080 --> 20:21.448
Scalpers are getting 50 or 60 bucks.

20:21.449 --> 20:22.866
50 or 60?!

20:22.867 --> 20:24.829
W...

20:24.830 --> 20:26.495
I could see these
people being that dumb.

20:26.496 --> 20:28.289
Dad, come on.

20:28.290 --> 20:30.079
Remember that time you and
your brother skipped school

20:30.080 --> 20:32.123
to see Babe Ruth play
against the Pirates?

20:32.124 --> 20:33.599
Oh, a day I'll never forget.

20:33.600 --> 20:36.000
The Great Bambino hit his
last home run in the majors.

20:36.010 --> 20:37.240
And as he rounded the bases,

20:37.250 --> 20:39.749
he ate 12 hot dogs and
finished a case of beer!

20:41.050 --> 20:43.263
Greatest athlete this
country will ever know.

20:43.264 --> 20:44.319
Exactly.

20:44.320 --> 20:46.431
And Led Zeppelin is our Babe Ruth.

20:46.432 --> 20:48.419
So don't rob us of countless memories

20:48.420 --> 20:49.940
we can bore our kids with.

20:51.620 --> 20:53.419
- Yeah! Thanks, Dad!
- Ah!

20:53.420 --> 20:54.840
I'll meet you at our seats.

20:54.850 --> 20:56.484
For some reason, I need a hot dog.

20:58.540 --> 21:00.019
I got one here! One here!

21:00.020 --> 21:01.399
Whoa, whoa, whoa! What are you doing?

21:01.400 --> 21:04.379
Memories are great, but
60 bucks is 60 bucks.

21:04.380 --> 21:06.460
You're abandoning your
brother to pocket some cash?

21:07.260 --> 21:08.680
Okay, tell you what...

21:08.690 --> 21:10.679
what if I used that cash to buy us both

21:10.680 --> 21:12.550
a nice steak dinner at Sizzler?

21:15.380 --> 21:16.840
We got one here!

21:16.850 --> 21:18.360
One! One here!

21:18.370 --> 21:20.079
Floor seating, section D!

21:20.080 --> 21:22.959
- 60 bucks!
- Section D, we've got one!

21:22.960 --> 21:25.539
- Best deal all night, all night!
- Hey, hey, buddy, you want it?

